# Project Title: India Post: A Bridge for Indian Diaspora to Access Things Indian

## Overview

This project is designed to help the Indian Diaspora connect with local sellers, MSMEs, and artisans in India. It aims to provide easy access to Indian products such as traditional attire, handicrafts, and Puja Samagri through India Post, enabling the diaspora to maintain their cultural ties. The platform will allow users to chat with sellers for customized orders, ensuring both quality and affordability.

## Features

- **User Registration**: Diaspora users and local sellers can register on the platform.
- **Product Listing**: A diverse range of Indian products from various regions (e.g., Puja Samagri from Kumartuli, Handicrafts from Santiniketan).
- **Real-time Chat**: Enables communication between users and sellers for personalized orders.
- **Global Shipping**: Integration with India Post for seamless global shipping.
- **AI-based Product Recommendations**: Recommends products based on user preferences and seasonal needs.
- **Custom Orders**: Allows customization of products based on user requirements.

## Technologies Used

- **Frontend**: HTML, CSS, JavaScript, EJS for templating.
- **Backend**: Node.js, Express.js for server-side logic.
- **Database**: MongoDB for data storage.
- **APIs**: Integration with India Post API for real-time shipping information.
- **Version Control**: Git and GitHub for version management.
- **Dependencies**:
  - Mongoose (for MongoDB interactions)
  - Express (for handling HTTP requests)
  - Socket.io (for real-time chat)

## Project Structure

```plaintext
